[We thank the ProMED subscriber who called this report to our attention.

Rift Valley fever (RVF) has been reported in Madagascar earlier this year (2021) (see Rift Valley fever - Madagascar: (TL) livestock, OIE 20210405.8288655) and previously in 2008 and 2009. That recent report indicated that 22 sheep and 110 goats had RVF. The above report indicates that more than 800 animals have been affected and the outbreak is expanding to new areas. It is not clear if these animal cases have been laboratory confirmed. The human cases are suspected as RVF. The increased surveillance for animal and human cases is prudent. - Mod.TY

